init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But now, they are beginning to make up for lost time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But the rest of the world is still wary of them and their intentions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It becomes a race to see who can out-innovate them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are out-innovated, out-maneuvered, and out of time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are a third world country, forever behind in the progress of technology and science.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They eventually become dependent on the world for answers to their problems.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They learn to survive on what the world gives them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They learn to appreciate every little thing they get from the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: People come to the United States for religious freedom.
